parameters:
Clea: Because I was able to meet Sophia-san, I was able to
come this far. Please walk the path of a new dream, the path
of a priest, together with Eleo-san.

Priestess Sophia: No, it's the opposite. You gently
embraced my weakness that I encountered when we met.

Priestess Sophia: Your greatsword is meant to carve a path
for tomorrow, for someone else... and for your own tomorrow
as well.
Clea: I promise, please... take care.

Mage Relm: Mages and priests don't get along... We've even
shattered such common sense!

Priestess Sophia: The days of unconventional adventures...
Even though there were many hardships, the memories are
filled with nothing but smiles.

Priestess Sophia: I really enjoyed the time I spent with
everyone, supporting Relm-chan's dream.

Mage Relm: ...Please stop saying things like it was fun,
sniffle. We're going to continue seeing each other, because
we're friends!

Thief Nora: I feel really lonely, even though we've always
been together... But, I also have a new dream for myself and
for Sophia-san.

Priestess Sophia: I feel lonely too... It's thanks to Nora-
chan and the others that I have come to experience such
emotions.

Priestess Sophia: Let's fulfill our dreams together, and
when times get tough, please rely on us, okay?

Thief Nora: I've decided not to cry, so I won't cry! The
most important thing is for both of us to stay strong. Let's
meet again in good health!

Priestess Sophia: Speaking of me, it's wine! Hehe, this is
the perfect place for a farewell.

Priestess Sophia: And for me, it's a place that we all won
together. It's a precious symbol of my journey.

\CL The Aftermath of Priestess SophiaShe actively extended
a helping hand to prostitutes and criminals. Due to her
approach, she was called the Priestess of the Goddess
Deirei and was loved.

\CL Speaking candidly about her own mistakes, combined with
her intelligence and beauty, many bards left behind numerous
works inspired by Sophia.

\CL Eleo and I shared a lot of time together, sometimes as a
teacher, sometimes as a friend.

\CL As the advisor, I was frequently invited to the royal
palace by King Rex. We had a good understanding and
maintained a platonic relationship until the end.

\CL She dedicated her entire life to the salvation of people
and remained single for her entire life.

\CL The Aftermath of Innkeeper GalaGathered by the beauty
and life of the famous priestess Sophia, the tavern became a
salon for artists and produced numerous celebrities.

\CL Innkeeper Gala and his descendants continued to protect
the tavern Trivos.

\CL Even after the collapse of the empire, the tavern known
as Old Trivos continued to be loved and produced renowned
artists.

Sister Eleo: I've been looking for you, Sophia-san! What on
earth made you come to the tavern instead of the church
first!

Sister Eleo: From now on, I will make sure you thoroughly
study what it means to be a priestess, so be prepared!

\CL The Aftermath of Sister EleoShe actively engaged in
preaching and charitable activities with Priestess Sophia.
She was a staunch advocate for the weak and even stood up
against those in power.

\CL Supported by the priestesses of the Three Goddesses and
the Adventurers' Guild, her activities would come to save
numerous people who were originally beyond salvation.

\CL She married a male follower of Terios and was blessed
with two children.

You can't come back, but are you really leaving the
tavern?
Clea (We haven't talked yet, have we?)

Priestess Sophia: Thank you so much. I will never forget
the days we spent traveling together.

Priestess Sophia: May the divine protection of the goddess
Imiserinos be with my dear friends...

Shopkeeper Gala: I will protect this shop forever, even if
my clan perishes. Together with everyone's names!

Clea: If I hadn't received a request from the guild back
then, I wouldn't have been able to meet Eleo-san or Sophia-
san.

Sister Eleo: At that time, I felt like I was being taken
away from Sophia-san... But because of the journey, I was
able to become even closer with Sophia-san.

Sister Eleo: I'm glad I was able to meet everyone. I wish
the blessings of the goddess Imiserinos upon all of you in
the future!

Mage Relm: It was quite a terrible meeting, but now I
consider myself recognized as a mage by the priestess,
right?
Sister Eleo: I feel the same... hehehe, ahahaha!

Mage Relm: Hehe, both mages and priests should do things
that are helpful for someone and for the people living in
the empire.

Thief Nora: Thank you for helping me save Goat-san! From
now on, I'll do my best as a mercenary!

Sister Eleo: It's a dangerous profession, so please be
careful not to get injured or sick.

Thief Nora: I'll come here at that time! Eleo-san and
Sophia-san will definitely heal you!
